  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Pixels between two layers are linked by the diffraction effect, and multiple phase layers are aligned sequentially along the optical axis to accomplish the desired mode conversion.",
    "The model of the spatial mode quantum gate is built and ready to be trained by iterative algorism on a computer.",
    "To learn the optimal phase layers that implement the desired operation on the experiment setup, we minimize the loss function of the deviation between the inference output field and the theoretical output field by the Adam gradient-descent algorithm 31 while the pixel phase values are updated in diffractive layers.",
    "The optimization result is obtained when the loss function converges.",
    "See Supplementary Note 1 for more details on the pattern generation."
  ],
